I have common header that i have to sent over every request using a retrofit 2 . So i have found this solution but this will repeat in every api .

 @Headers({
        "Accept: application/vnd.yourapi.v1.full+json",
        "User-Agent: Your-App-Name"
    })
    @GET("/tasks/{task_id}")
    Call&lt;Task&gt; getTask(@Path("task_id") long taskId);

I found that anyway.

OkHttpClient.Builder builder = new OkHttpClient.Builder();
 builder.addInterceptor(new Interceptor() {
            @Override
            public Response intercept(Chain chain) throws IOException {
                Request request = chain.request().newBuilder().
                        addHeader("key", "value").build();
                return chain.proceed(request);
            }
        });

This will add header.
